<title>USA: Two investors charged with lying to SEC - NYT.</title>
<headline>Two investors charged with lying to SEC - NYT.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-05-15</dateline>
<text>
<p>Two New Jersey investors have been charged with lying in testimony they gave about their trading in options on Lotus Development Corp, the New York Times said.</p>
<p>In its Friday editions, the Times said the charges stem from a federal investigation into possible insider trading in shares of Lotus before it was acquired by IBM in 1995.</p>
<p>Robert Kowalskie of Whippany, N.J., pleaded not guilty on Wednesday to charges that he obstructed justice, committed perjury and got someone else to lie to the Securities and Exchange Commission, the Times said.</p>
